---

## 2. Project Summary and Background

### Objectives & Scope

* Make planning social activities among students faster and easier
* Allow users to share their availability and suggest group events inside the calendar
* Support simple yes/no workflows for group coordination (accept/decline)
* Target users: Ewha Womans University computer science students and their friends (not corporate teams)
* Focus on real-time free-time matching and group proposal features

### Necessity & Background

* **Problem:** Students waste significant time coordinating plans with friends, often failing due to mismatched schedules and fragmented chat discussions
* **Existing tools:** (Google Calendar, KakaoTalk) are not designed for group social planning; either too individual-focused or lead to chat clutter/confusion
* **Gap:** No tool provides a clear, mutual view of friends’ free time or a seamless workflow for proposing/accepting group activities in a social context

---

## 3. Target Users & Research Basis

### Target Users

* Ewha Womans University Computer Science students
* Students in project-based courses and club activities
* Groups who frequently plan meals, meetings, or outings

### User Research (Survey/Interviews)

Peers reported issues with:

* Clashing schedules
* Messy group chats (KakaoTalk, etc.)
* Needing multiple apps to agree on a plan

**Key pain points:** Inability to easily see mutual availability; frustration from inefficient, repetitive messaging

---

## 4. Problems, Needs, and Proposed Solution

### Key Problems to Solve

* Difficult to find compatible times for group activities
* Excessive, repetitive back-and-forth messaging
* No easy way to see friends' real-time availability
* No built-in group proposal/acceptance feature in existing tools
* Social plans collapse due to "coordination friction"

### User Needs

* Visual, glanceable mutual free time
* Simple interface to suggest/respond to events
* Real-time, always-synced updates across friends’ devices
* Lightweight, student-friendly, privacy-respecting tool

### Proposed Solution

**ScheduleSync** is a browser-based web app with these capabilities:

* Users register and share their calendar with friends
* Instantly see friends' free/busy slots in real time
* Suggest group activities with a single click; friends accept/decline in-app
* All coordination happens inside the calendar (not scattered chats)
* Powered by Firebase for real-time sync and easy sharing
* Designed for casual, fast social planning (not complex enterprise meetings)

---

## 5. Comparison with Existing Projects/Services

| Tool                       | Strengths                                                                                                                                          | Weaknesses                                                                                                     |
| -------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Google Calendar            | Great for managing individual time                                                                                                                 | No friend-to-friend mutual availability; lacks social features                                                 |
| KakaoTalk/Other Schedulers | Familiar group chat for Korean students                                                                                                            | Message clutter, confusion, lost info; requires extra tools for polls/calendars; no visual mutual availability |
| **ScheduleSync**           | Real-time, friend-based free time sharing; event suggestions and responses inside the calendar; all-in-one workflow for students and social groups | (N/A)                                                                                                          |

---

## 6. Main Features

| # | Feature Name            | Description                                                                  |
| - | ----------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1 | Personal Weekly Planner | Each user manages their own events, classes, and time blocks                 |
| 2 | Friend-Based Sharing    | Users choose which friends can see their free/busy status                    |
| 3 | Group Event Suggestion  | Anyone can propose an activity, select invitees, and propose times           |
| 4 | One-Click Response      | Invitees accept/decline events in the app; mutual availability is visualized |
| 5 | Real-Time Updates       | All changes update instantly for all friends (via Firebase)                  |
| 6 | Lightweight Web UI      | Runs in browser, easy to use, no app install required                        |
| 7 | Privacy Controls        | Users control which friends can see their schedule details                   |

---

## 7. System Design and Architecture

**Overall Structure:**

* **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React

  * Schedule input, calendar display, friend view, event suggestion, response interface

**Application Logic:**

* Modular JavaScript:

  * `app.js`: Event and calendar logic
  * `auth.js`: User login/authentication
  * `suggestions.js`: Proposing/responding to group events

**Backend:**

* **Firebase (Firestore, Auth, Hosting):**

  * Stores user events, manages authentication, handles real-time updates for all users

**Workflow:**

* User logs in, creates/edits events
* Friends’ free/busy slots appear on calendar
* Suggest group events; responses are tracked and visible for all
* All updates sync instantly for everyone

---

## 8. Development Plan and Current Progress

### Development Plan

* **Phase 1: Setup & Planning**

  * Establish GitHub repository
  * Define file structure (`index.html`, `style.css`, `app.js`)
  * Initialize Firebase project, test Firestore connection

* **Phase 2: Core Functionality**

  * Event creation form (add schedule blocks)
  * Display events on personal calendar
  * Implement Firebase Auth (login/signup)

* **Phase 3: Friend & Suggestion Modules**

  * Implement friend list and sharing logic
  * Enable event suggestion, acceptance/decline features

### Current Progress

* Project structure and module outline are complete
* Firebase backend configured, initial connectivity tested
* All planned features are organized and documented
* UI/UX structure designed (low-fidelity wireframe)
* No functional UI implemented yet—feature development is next

